	<Title>
		Have a black eye? Here&apos;s what to do
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Most black eye injuries aren&apos;t serious. The discoloration is caused by bleeding under the skin around the eye. To take care of a black eye: Gently apply a cold pack or a cloth filled with ice to the area around your eye. Don&apos;t press on your eye. Repeat several times a day for one to two days. Seek medical care immediately if you have vision problems, severe pain, or bleeding in your eye or from your nose.&lt;/p&gt;
